# Shell scripts must keep LF endings in the working tree. On a CRLF-checkout platform
# (this repo is developed under WSL against a Windows-mounted path) git would otherwise
# rewrite them, and bash then reads `set -euo pipefail\r` as an invalid option name and
# aborts the script on line 1 — which cost a benchmark battery two silent no-op runs
# before anyone noticed the \r.
*.sh        text eol=lf
gradlew     text eol=lf
*.py        text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf
